text: Harumi Kohara (born 24 June 1965) is a Japanese badminton player. She competed in women's singles and women's doubles at the 1992 Summer Olympics in Barcelona. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1965 births Category:Living people Category:Japanese female badminton players Category:Olympic badminton players of Japan Category:Badminton players at the 1992 Summer Olympics Category:Asian Games medalists in badminton Category:Badminton players at the 1986 Asian Games Category:Asian Games silver medalists for Japan Category:Medalists at the 1986 Asian Games
